subSubSection.paragraph:
Skeleton.
(
Figs 37–e
) In cross section (
Fig. 37b
) from outside to atrium, there is a cortical skeleton of giant tri- and tetractines (
Fig. 37c
), a choanosomal skeleton (
Fig. 37d
) of small thin equiangular and equiradiate tri- and tetractines, and an atrial membrane (
Fig. 37e
) supported by small sagittal (‘abruptly’-angled) tri- and tetractines.
